# This script updates the git submodules to the latest version of their respective repositories.
# It performs the following actions:
# 1. Initializes any submodules that have not yet been initialized.
# 2. Updates the remote tracking branches for all submodules.
# 3. Fetches any new changes from the remote repositories.
# 4. Pulls those changes into the local submodule repositories.
# This is useful for ensuring that all submodules are up-to-date with the latest changes.
